{
  "What is a rational expression?": "",
  "A fraction where the numerator and/or denominator are polynomials": "",
  "How do you simplify?": "",
  "Factor both numerator and denominator, then cancel common factors": "",
  "When is a rational expression undefined?": "",
  "When the denominator equals zero": "",
  "What are excluded values?": "",
  "The values of x that make the denominator zero": "",
  "Simplify: (x² − 9)/(x + 3)": "",
  "(x+3)(x−3)/(x+3) = x − 3, where x ≠ −3": "",
  "Simplify: (2x)/(4x²)": "",
  "1/(2x), where x ≠ 0": "",
  "Simplify: (x² + 5x + 6)/(x + 2)": "",
  "(x+2)(x+3)/(x+2) = x + 3, where x ≠ −2": "",
  "Can you cancel terms (not factors)?": "",
  "No — only cancel common FACTORS, not separate terms": "",
  "Why must you state excluded values?": "",
  "Because certain x-values make the denominator zero (undefined)": "",
  "Find excluded values: (x + 1)/(x² − 4)": "",
  "x ≠ 2 and x ≠ −2 (where x² − 4 = 0)": ""
}